-- Sub-Saharan Africa Stocks: Barclays Bank of Kenya, Equity Bank
-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 2012-02-16T15:44:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-16/sub-saharan-africa-stocks-barclays-bank-of-kenya-equity-bank.html
The  FTSE/Namibia Overall Index (FTN098) 
slumped for a third day, dropped 1.5 percent to 907.06 in
Windhoek at the close of trading.  Kenya’s  All-Share Index (NSEASI)  gained for a second day, increasing
0.5 percent to 54.91 in Nairobi. Mauritius’s  SEMDEX Index (SEMDEX) 
retreated 0.2 percent to 1,820.54. The  Nigerian Stock Exchange
All-Share Index (NGSEINDX)  fell less than 0.1 percent to 20,314.08 in
Lagos, according to a statement on the bourse’s website.  The following shares were active in sub-Saharan Africa,
excluding  South Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Barclays Bank of Kenya Ltd.  (BCBL KN), the country’s
second-biggest lender by market value, jumped 4.8 percent to 13
shillings, after declaring a special dividend and announcing
profit excluding one-time items increased.  Equity Bank Ltd. (EQBNK)  , Kenya’s largest lender by
market value, extended gains for a ninth day, climbing 0.5
percent to 19 shillings, its longest rally in three years, on
speculation its full-year earnings will grow.  “It is in anticipation of the release of the full-year
results; guys are expecting very good results,” Caleb Mutai, an
analyst at Nairobi-based Tsavo Securities Ltd., said in a phone
interview today.  For Related News and Information:  To contact the reporter on this story:
